		<div id="comment_body_64188514">Boeing was supposed to adopt Six-Sigma when my old GE Information Services boss, Jim McNerney, became the boss. Six-Sigma was a quality improvement program that Chairman Jack Welch pushed through GE. It reminds us that fixing a defect early in production is far cheaper than having to recall product after the defects cause the product to fail as customers use it. When I was training as a Six-Sig "Green Belt", the instructors warned us, over and over, against defects that might cause an air-liner to crash. A</div>
